%I A394893 #6 Apr 13 2026 15:18:30
%S A394893 1,2,1,4,5,23,76,554
%N A394893 Number of integers x in range A002110(n-1) .. A002110(n)-1 such that the u-th arithmetic derivative of A276086(x) is zero for some u, and A328114(x) = prime(n-1), where A002110(n) is the n-th primorial, and A328114 gives the largest digit in the primorial base.
%C A394893 Question: What is the eventual growth rate of this sequence?
%C A394893 Computing the term a(9) would be require almost as much resources as computing of the term A351071(8). See further comments in that sequence.
%o A394893 (PARI) A394893(n) = A394890_sq(n,prime(n)-1);
%Y A394893 Right edge of triangle A394890.
%Y A394893 Cf. A002110, A003415, A276086, A328114, A328116, A351071.
%K A394893 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A394893 1,2
